<Layout title="Terms & Conditions - Boundless Travelogues">
  <section class="container fade-in" style="max-width: 900px;">
    <h1>Terms & Conditions</h1>
    <p style="color: #666; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Last Updated: November 17, 2025</p>
    
    <div style="line-height: 1.8;">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">1. Trip Planning & Schedule</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The trip plan and schedule must be finalized before the trip commences.</li>
        <li>No changes to the itinerary will be accepted once the trip has been confirmed.</li>
        <li>Any modifications requested before confirmation may be subject to additional charges.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">2. Participant Responsibilities</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>All participants must strictly follow instructions and guidelines provided by the tour coordinator.</li>
        <li>Participants must carry valid ID proof (Aadhar Card, Passport, Student ID, etc.).</li>
        <li>Any health conditions, allergies, or medical treatments must be disclosed prior to booking.</li>
        <li>Participants under medical treatment should travel only after consulting with their physician.</li>
        <li>Participants must bring their own prescribed medications.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">3. Liability & Responsibility</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Boundless Travelogues is not responsible for issues arising from participant negligence or violation of guidelines.</li>
        <li>The company is not liable for loss or damage to personal belongings during the trip.</li>
        <li>Participants are responsible for their own safety and must follow all safety instructions.</li>
        <li>Any damage to hotel property, vehicles, or other facilities will be charged to the participant.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">4. Force Majeure</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Due to unpredictable circumstances (natural calamities, political unrest, strikes, etc.), trip schedules may be modified.</li>
        <li>Participants will be notified immediately of any such changes.</li>
        <li>The company will make best efforts to provide alternative arrangements but is not liable for refunds in such cases.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">5. Payment Terms</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>An agreement must be signed before trip confirmation.</li>
        <li>A pre-fixed advance amount must be paid on the date of agreement.</li>
        <li>The remaining balance must be paid before or during the trip as per agreed terms.</li>
        <li>The total trip cost is calculated based on the number of participants.</li>
        <li>Changes in participant numbers may affect the total cost.</li>
        <li>Bus booking will be done only after the agreement is signed and advance is paid.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">6. Pricing & Rate Changes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>All prices are subject to change due to fluctuations in ticket rates, taxes, or hotel charges.</li>
        <li>Any such changes will be communicated with genuine proof and documentation.</li>
        <li>After the agreement is signed, no changes in rates or schedules will be entertained unless mutually agreed.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">7. Cancellation & Refund Policy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Cancellations made 30+ days before departure: 80% refund (20% processing fee)</li>
        <li>Cancellations made 15-29 days before departure: 50% refund</li>
        <li>Cancellations made 7-14 days before departure: 25% refund</li>
        <li>Cancellations made less than 7 days before departure: No refund</li>
        <li>Refunds will be processed within 15-30 business days.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">8. Accommodation & Meals</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Accommodation will be provided as per the package selected.</li>
        <li>Room allocation is subject to availability and hotel policies.</li>
        <li>Meals will be provided as specified in the itinerary.</li>
        <li>Special dietary requirements must be informed at the time of booking.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">9. Transportation</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Transportation will be provided as per the package (bus, train, or flight).</li>
        <li>Seat allocation in buses is on a first-come, first-served basis unless specified.</li>
        <li>Participants must adhere to departure timings; the company is not responsible for missed departures.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">10. Code of Conduct</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Participants must maintain decorum and respect local customs and traditions.</li>
        <li>Consumption of alcohol or prohibited substances is strictly forbidden during educational tours.</li>
        <li>Any illegal activities will result in immediate termination from the tour without refund.</li>
        <li>Participants must respect fellow travelers and tour staff.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">11. Support & Assistance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Tour coordinators are available throughout the trip for assistance.</li>
        <li>Participants should feel free to express any discomfort or issues to the coordinator.</li>
        <li>24/7 emergency support is available during active tours.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">12. Agreement Verification</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>All trip details and itinerary must be verified before signing the agreement.</li>
        <li>The agreement should be signed in the presence of authorized representatives.</li>
        <li>Both parties must retain a copy of the signed agreement.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">13. Governing Law</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>These terms and conditions are governed by the laws of India.</li>
        <li>Any disputes will be subject to the jurisdiction of Kerala courts.</li>
      </ul>
      
